  <title>Concern Worldwide:Promoting Equal Access to Education (for Girls and Most Vulnerable Children in Nsanje District in Malawi).</title>
  <description>This project will improve access to education and encourage pupil retention , particularly for girls and vulnerable children ,in the district of Nsanje, southern Malawi, an area often neglected by NGOs. The project will work with the community to improve the quality of education at primary schools through the promotion of community participation in education. Outcomes will be reduced absenteeism and increased pupil retention, especially girls in the upper classes and also adoption by teachers of more child-friendly and gender sensitive approaches . The project will conduct training and sensitisation involving parents, pupils, Head Teachers, Primary Education Advisors and mother groups directly benefiting an estimated 18,739 pupils in 25 schools.</description>
